$ IEEE-754 (Floating Point Arithmetic - float/double etc)

{ ieee-754.c

This is a simple c program that prints the binary representation of a `double`. A `0` bit is represented with a `.`. An exponent-`1` bit
is represented with an `E`. A mantissa-`1` bit is represented with a `M`. The negative sign bit is represented with a `S`.

gh|about-IEEE-754|/ieee-754.c||

The program prints
code {
